<ol><li>Since the intensity of light received from a star depends on its distance from Earth according to the&nbsp;<b>inverse square law</b>.</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>ratio of</b>&nbsp;star X at a distance of 10pc with an identical star at distance&nbsp;\(d\)\[\frac{I_X}{I_Y}=\left(\frac{d}{10}\right)^2\]</li><li>The difference between their&nbsp;<b>apparent magnitude</b>.\[m_Y-m_X=5\log\frac{d}{10}\]</li></ol>